{
  "text": "where the first term is defined in Cycle P-H and the last two terms are defined in Cycle H-H. Note that the third term uses Mean Average Error instead of Dice, because if the target mask is black, then given any result mask, Dice loss will always produce 1. L GAN 1 is the least squares discriminator loss over synthetic images [CITATION_1] :",
